@startuml

title BBQ Grilling Recipe Book - Reference Data Flow

actor User
participant "Dashboard" as Dashboard
participant "Reference Menu" as Menu
participant "Meat Temperatures" as TempView
participant "Techniques Guide" as TechView
participant "Reference Service" as RefService
participant "Reference Controller" as RefAPI
participant "Database" as DB

== View Meat Temperature Guide ==
User -> Dashboard: Navigate to resources
activate Dashboard
Dashboard -> Menu: Display reference menu
activate Menu
Menu --> User: Show menu options
deactivate Dashboard

User -> Menu: Select "Meat Temperatures"
Menu -> TempView: Load temperature guide
activate TempView
TempView -> RefService: getMeatTemperatures()
activate RefService
RefService -> RefAPI: GET /api/reference/meat-temperatures
activate RefAPI
RefAPI -> DB: Query meat temperature data
activate DB
note right of DB
Temperature data includes:
- Meat type (beef, pork, chicken, etc.)
- Cut of meat
- Doneness level (rare, medium, well)
- Target temperature
- USDA safe minimum temp
end note
DB --> RefAPI: Return temperature data
deactivate DB
RefAPI --> RefService: 200 OK with temperature data
deactivate RefAPI
RefService --> TempView: Temperature data
deactivate RefService
TempView --> User: Display temperature guide
note right of User
View organized by:
- Meat type categories
- Visual temperature chart
- Safety guidelines
- Doneness descriptions
end note
deactivate Menu

== Search Temperature by Meat Type ==
User -> TempView: Search for specific meat
activate TempView
TempView -> TempView: Filter temperature data
TempView --> User: Show filtered results
deactivate TempView

== View BBQ Techniques Guide ==
User -> Menu: Navigate back to resources
activate Menu
User -> Menu: Select "BBQ Techniques"
Menu -> TechView: Load techniques guide
activate TechView
TechView -> RefService: getTechniques()
activate RefService
RefService -> RefAPI: GET /api/reference/techniques
activate RefAPI
RefAPI -> DB: Query technique data
activate DB
note right of DB
Technique data includes:
- Technique name
- Description
- Step-by-step instructions
- Tips and best practices
- Common mistakes to avoid
- Related recipes
end note
DB --> RefAPI: Return technique data
deactivate DB
RefAPI --> RefService: 200 OK with technique data
deactivate RefAPI
RefService --> TechView: Technique data
deactivate RefService
TechView --> User: Display techniques guide
note right of User
Techniques organized by:
- Cooking method (direct, indirect)
- Grilling techniques
- Smoking techniques
- Temperature control
- Wood selection
end note
deactivate Menu

== View Technique Details ==
User -> TechView: Click on technique
activate TechView
TechView -> TechView: Expand technique details
TechView --> User: Show detailed instructions
note right of User
Detailed view includes:
- Overview
- Equipment needed
- Step-by-step process
- Temperature guidelines
- Time estimates
- Pro tips
- Video tutorials (optional)
end note

== Apply Technique to Recipe ==
User -> TechView: Click "See Recipes"
TechView -> RefService: getRecipesByTechnique(techniqueId)
activate RefService
RefService -> RefAPI: GET /api/recipes?technique={techniqueId}
activate RefAPI
RefAPI -> DB: Query recipes using technique
activate DB
DB --> RefAPI: Return recipe list
deactivate DB
RefAPI --> RefService: 200 OK with recipes
deactivate RefAPI
RefService --> TechView: Recipe list data
deactivate RefService
TechView --> User: Display related recipes
deactivate TechView

== Access Quick Reference During Cooking ==
User -> TempView: Access during active cooking
activate TempView
note right of TempView
Quick access features:
- Pinned to sidebar
- Mobile-friendly layout
- Offline availability
- Quick search
end note
TempView --> User: Display quick reference overlay
User -> TempView: Check target temperature
TempView --> User: Show temperature info
deactivate TempView

@enduml
